cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CV. 

The paper deals with designing sparse pose-graph SLAM problems, which is a problem in robotics and control systems. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also heavily relies on graph theory and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions using the dataset for visual SLAM, which could place it in cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
